# **Redefining Your Limits**

What do you allow to define the limits on your life?

Jennifer Bricker is an American acrobat and aerialist. The trouble is, she has no legs. Even still, she has learned to push through incredible obstacles to get to where she is today.

In a telling interview, she said, “*‘Can't’* is not part of your vocabulary. If you just put your mind to it, you can do it."

Her parents empowered her to live without limits, which opened her up to more possibilities than most children who even live in normal circumstances. She said, "If you were never given limits, then you think you can do anything."

At seven years old, she decided to become a tumbler and by the time she was in high school, she had become the Illinois state tumbling champion.

That was only the beginning.

What are your limits? 

* Is it your age?  
* Is it your ability or the incredible odds set against you?  
* Is it that it has never been done before?

What if you lived as though these limits didn’t exist? What would your life look like then?

What perspective would you have to take in life, if you saw yourself as literally limit-less?
